Log In

 

Visit https://conservationspace.com. Upon loading you will see the Log In screen.

To access the system:

  1.  Fill in your user name 
  2.  Fill in your password
  3.  Click Sign In

You can mark the “Remember me on this computer” check box to automatically go to your personal dashboard upon visiting https://conservationspace.com.1

1 – Depends on your browser settings.

Authentication

 

After successfully logging into the system you will be taken to your personal dashboard. This is the screen where you can see your user information and begin navigating through the main menu.   

Log Out

To log out of the system:

  1.  Select User Section in the upper right corner of the screen
  2.  Select Logout from the drop-down menu 

Session Expired

 

There is a system configuration which will log a user out automatically due to inactivity. This configuration can be set to 30 minutes, 15 minutes, etc.

What happens once your session has expired?

  • You are logged out automatically and the system login screen is displayed.

  • You may log back in in order to continue working.

 

Troubleshooting the User Log In

 

If you cannot log in because of authentication problems you may want to verify the following:

      1. Remember that passwords are case sensitive; in other words, the system
          recognizes ‘password’ and ‘PaSsWoRd’ as two different passwords. Is your [Caps Lock] indicator on?

     2. Did you use the right user credentials?

If you have made the above checks, but still cannot log in, contact your system administrator; your password can still be recovered or reset.
